here is rest-auth doccumentation: https://django-rest-auth.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configuration.html
In settings.py change:
##put this in basic login section to prevent user login without verification
ACCOUNT_EMAIL_VERIFICATION = 'mandatory'

##base url of your app:
BASE_URL='https://backend-rafi.herokuapp.com'

##put default avatar link here:
DISPLAY_PIC_DEFAULT_URL='https://graph.facebook.com/2008681126092072/picture?type=large'

##your hosing provider
EMAIL_HOST = 'smtp.gmail.com'
##put yours email
EMAIL_HOST_USER = 'your email'
##put your password
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD = 'password'

If you use gmail, Chage the settings in your google account by 'allowing unknown apps' and prevent capcha during login.

